GPT: GUID Partition Table
GUID: Globally Unique Identifier
EFI: Extensible Firmware Interface
UEFI: Unified Extensible Firmware Interface

- designed to replace the MBR partitioning scheme method

- at the start of a GUID Partition Table there's a protective Master Boot Record (PMBR) to protect against GPT-unaware software. The PMBR has a bootstrap code area, like an ordinary MBR,  which can be used for BIOS/GPT booting with boot loaders that support it. 
